article.headline: Hartford 53, Stony Brook 51
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP)Joe Zeglinski scored 18 points and Hartford edged Stony Brook 53-51 for its fourth straight victory Thursday. Morgan Sabia scored 16 points for the Hawks (14-13, 8-4 America East). Michael Tyree had 13 points for the Seawolves (4-20, 1-11), who lost their 10th straight. Emanuel Neto added 12 points. Tyree's 3-point basket pulled Stony Brook to within 13-11 at 6:61 of the first half. The Hawks scored seven straight, five by Sabia, to go up 20-11 at 4:00. Sabia gave Hartford a 48-40 lead on a layup with 7:46 left in the second half. Stony Brook then went on a 9-3 run, capped by Tyree jumper's to get within 51-49 with 38 seconds to play. Warren McClendon sealed the win with two free throws with five seconds to play.
